  "riddle": "1. Seek the golden arches that symbolize the world's most beloved fast-food chain. How many types of locations and branches under this franchise can you uncover?\n\n2. A force so powerful, it stretches across borders and cultures. Find the page that discusses the dual nature of this phenomenon — how many subsections are dedicated to its support and criticism?\n\n3. To navigate the implications of the global sphere you just explored, distill the count of its subsections in clue 2 to a single digit. What remains?\n\n4. Venture to the land known for its samba and soccer. Discover the people who call this vast nation their home. What number will you find?\n\n5. A city that lights the way for romance and love! Delve into its entry to reveal how many souls reside there as of January 2026.\n\n6. Rising above the Seine, behold the City of Light. What height does this historic place reach above the sea?\n\n7. Beyond the Eiffel's gaze thrives knowledge. How many libraries can you spot nearby this enchanting metropolis?\n\n8. Harness the wisdom from clues 6 and 7: take the absolute difference between the elevation you discovered and the count of libraries. What number arises from this combination?\n\n9. Now turn your gaze to a bustling metropolis known for its neon lights and culinary delights. Count the hospitals that shelter the residents near latitude 35.68972; what is your total?\n\n10. Finally, consolidate your findings: from clue 1 (the types of locations) subtract the population from clue 5, then reduce that result modulo 10. What single digit have you calculated after this journey?",
